==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tribasic
<hw>Tri*ba"sic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>basic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Capable of neutralizing three molecules of a monacid base, or their
equivalent; having three hydrogen atoms capable of replacement by basic
elements on radicals; -- said of certain acids; thus, citric acid is a
<xex>tribasic</xex> acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tribble</ent>⟦br⟧
